| Investment Companies Backing Patent Trolls                         |
|   from the arms-merchants-in-the-patent-wars dept.                 |
|   posted by kdawson on Tuesday April 24, @20:01 (Patents)          |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/24/2247246          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

greenbird sends us to Forbes for an account of [0]billions in investments
flowing to US patent troll companies. One example is [1]DeepNines, who is
suing McAfee over a [2]patent that covers combining an IDS and firewall
in a single device. The patent was filed on May 17, 2000 and issued on
June 6, 2006. No prior art for that, no siree. DeepNines is funded by "an
$8 million zero-coupon note to Altitude Capital Partners, a New York City
private equity firm, promising in return a cut of any winnings stemming
from the lawsuit. The payout is based on a formula that grants Altitude a
percentage that decreases with a bigger award."

Discuss this story at:
    http://yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/24/2247246

Links:
    0. http://www.forbes.com/free_forbes/2007/0507/044.html?partner=yahoomag
    1. http://www.deepnines.com/
    2. http://patft.uspto.gov/netacgi/nph-Parser?Sect1=PTO1&Sect2=HITOFF&d=PALL&p=1&u=%2Fnetahtml%2FPTO%2Fsrchnum.htm&r=1&f=G&l=50&s1=7,058,976.PN.&OS=PN/7,058,976&RS=PN/7,058,976


