gnaremooz writes to tell us that The Register recently [0]sat down with
Karl Auerbach, the last publicly elected member of the ICANN board, and
discussed some of the more recent developments. "Perhaps my main point of
view regarding what I want to do for the net is expressed in my
[1]presentation [PPT] "From Barnstorming to Boeing - Transforming the
Internet Into a Lifeline Utility" ([2]speakers notes avilable [PDF]).
I've long been interested in making the net a solid utility, and I have a
great deal of sympathy for the folks who have to go out and fix things at
3am. I'm very interested in building tools for those folks."

