+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Why Are T1 Lines Still Expensive?                                  |
|   from the unpredictable-market-forces dept.                       |
|   posted by Cliff on Wednesday April 25, @17:55 (Networking)       |
|   http://ask.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/25/207216           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

badfrog asks: "Over the last 10 years, DSL and cable modem has upped its
speed (although in some instances only slightly) and dropped its price.
However, the price of a T1 has stayed almost exactly the same. If you had
asked me 10 years ago, I would have predicted any geek that wanted to
would have fiber or their own T1 line to the house by now. What is with
this sad state of affairs that a 'business class' 1.544Mbit connection is
hundreds of dollars more than a 6Mbit cable connection? Is it a
legitimate case that a high upload rate should increase cost so
significantly?"

Discuss this story at:
    http://ask.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/25/207216


+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Ohio University Blocks P2P File Sharing                            |
|   from the forward-thinking-at-its-best dept.                      |
|   posted by ScuttleMonkey on Wednesday April 25, @18:27 (The Intern|
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/25/219257           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

After receiving the [0]highest number of notices from the RIAA about P2P
file sharing, Ohio University has announced a policy that [1]restricts
all fire sharing on the campus network. Some file-sharing programs that
could trigger action are Ares, Azureus, BitTorrent, BitLord, KaZaA,
LimeWire, Shareaza and uTorrent. Claiming that this effort is 'to ensure
that every student, faculty member and researcher has access to the
computer resources they need,' is this another nail in the coffin of
internet freedom in American universities or a needed step to prevent
illegal fire sharing?

Discuss this story at:
    http://yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/25/219257

